  "text": "Kidney tissue levels of acid-soluble thiols and reduced GSH were determined calorimetrically at 412 nm [CITATION_1] . Homogenates were precipitated with trichloroacetic acid, and after centrifugation, supernatants were used for the estimation of protein thiols (Protein-SH) expressed as μmol/mg wet tissue.",
